-- Keiko Fujimori Takes Lead in Peru Presidential Race, El Comercio Poll Says
-- John Quigley
-- 2010-06-20T15:59:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-20/keiko-fujimori-takes-lead-in-peru-presidential-race-el-comercio-poll-says.html

          
          
             Keiko Fujimori , a congresswoman and
daughter of jailed former Peruvian president  Alberto Fujimori ,
has taken the lead in a poll before the presidential election in
April 2011, El Comercio  reported .  
 Fujimori, 35, would receive 22 percent of the vote if
elections were held tomorrow, 4 percentage points more than last
month, the Lima-based newspaper said, citing survey group  Ipsos
Apoyo .  
 Support for Lima Mayor  Luis Castaneda  slipped 1 percentage
point to 21 percent. Opposition politician  Ollanta Humala  would
get 13 percent of the vote and former president  Alejandro Toledo 
would receive 12 percent, the newspaper said.  
 The survey of 1,200 people this month in 17 Peruvian cities
had an error margin of plus or minus 4.4 percent for Lima and
2.8 percent overall, according to El Comercio.  
